data.enText: the place at a theatre, cinema/movie theater, etc. where the tickets are sold
The movie has been a huge box-office success (= many people have been to see it) .

tr: the office where tickets of admission are sold
total admission receipts for an entertainment

value.def: The box office in a theatre, cinema, or concert hall is the place where the tickets are sold.
value.tran: （剧院、电影院或音乐厅的）售票处

example.ex: The film has taken £180 million at the box office...
example.tran: 这部电影票房收入已达1.8亿英镑。

example.ex: The film was a huge box-office success.

value.def: When people talk about the box office, they are referring to the degree of success of a film or play in terms of the number of people who go to watch it or the amount of money it makes.
value.tran: （电影等的）卖座情况，票房收入
